text:
Yeah tbh before learning the mechanics, the GTA police chase system can be a pain in the ass. 
Like logically, there shouldn't just be random copcars in some middle-of-nowhere backroads - but the game spawns them wherever and they always seem to be homing towards the player, even when not in view. 

Not much help that chat keeps saying to go into the subway systems and that underground tunnel, when she doesn't have the locations memorized and it's not exactly easy to just pick from a map or find randomly.

In the end I was glad she persisted and got it done though! As well as seemed to learn the mechanic of staying away from their vision cones when not in them. That's plenty of personal XP earned there! :_guWAT:
